camp.PredictiveHelp.Minlinesperagent.hel: The lower limit set for number of calls to dial per agent. If this value is set as 2 and there are 30 agents, the number of contacts per iteration is limited to 60.
camp.PredictiveHelp.Maxlinesperagent.hel: The upper limit set for number of calls to dial per agent. If this value is set as 4 and there are 30 agents, the number of contacts per iteration is limited to 120.

camp.PredictiveHelp.Abandonedrate.help: Maximum Abanadoned rate set so that NCD calculation will be resetThis setting limits the call abandoned rate to this value by reducing the number of calls to dial.
camp.PredictiveHelp.Noofcallstosample.he: The number of calls taken for sampling by the predictive algorithm.
camp.PredictiveHelp.DialrequestIteration: The duration between two iterations for the campaign to deliver contacts to the dialer.
camp.PredictiveHelp.InitialSeed.title: Initial Seed Value:
camp.PredictiveHelp.InitialSeed.help: The number of contacts, per agent, to be delivered to the dialer for the first iteration after a campaign has started executing for the day. This value is applicable only till the first call is successfully patched between the agent and the customer. For example, if you select 3, the campaign initially delivers three contacts for every Ready agent.
camp.PredictiveHelp.InitialSeesIteration: The number of iterations that the Initial Seed Value applies to.
camp.PredictiveHelp.Lossfactor.title: Loss Factor:
camp.PredictiveHelp.Lossfactor.help: The factor by which to decrease the dialing rate in case success calls are received faster than expected. For example, if the three contacts delivered as per the previous iteration are patched to agents and call completed earlier than expected, this loss factor (say 1) is applied to decrease the contacts to two (from three). This helps in reducing the abandoned calls.
camp.PredictiveHelp.Gainfactor.title: Gain Factor:
camp.PredictiveHelp.Gainfactor.help: The factor by which to increase the dialing rate in case success calls are not received as expected. For example, if the three contacts delivered as per the previous iteration are not successful, this gain factor (say 1) is applied to increase the contacts to four (from three).

camp.PredictiveHelp.Timelimit.help: The time limit, in milliseconds, for the application to detect CPA. For example, if the CPA does not detect the voice within this limit, it considered as a human voice. Select values between 1000 and 5000 milliseconds.

camp.PredictiveHelp.Tones.title: Tones:
camp.PredictiveHelp.Tones.help: Select the Tones and the corresponding frequencies next. The single tone frequencies to be detected and the tolerance levels for each frequency. This is an json object with the each key being a name for the frequency and value being the frequency and tolerance in Hertz, separated by a pipe(|).From the CPA Event drop-down list, select an event. agent.RequiresDisposition.content: A campaign specific flag that notifies the Agent Desktop for a mandatory disposition. Appropriate implementation should be done in the Agent Desktop application.
agent.DNCPeriod.content: A campaign-specific property available for the API consumer to decide the DNC period. In an Agent Desktop, when agents dispose the contact as DNC using the SetCallResults API method, it expects the DNC period. Using this property, the application can decide the value for “DNCBlockStartDate” and “DNCBlockEndDate”.
agent.Permanent.Content: 1) Permanent - If this option is enabled, the contact is marked as DNC permanently by the system. The user sends the End Date as 20 years from the Start Date.
agent.SpeceficDay.Content: 2) Specific Days - If this option is enabled, the contact is marked as DNC for a specific duration
agent.DNC(days): ◉ DNC (days) - This value determines the number of days that the contact is to be marked as DNC. The default value is 1 day; the maximum value is 3650 days (that is, 10yrs).
agent.EOD: ◉ EOD - If this flag is enabled, End Time shall be calculated till midnight of the end date; else the End Time is calculated as days x 24 hours.
agent.AgentSelection: 3) Agent Selection - This option allows the agent to choose a DNC duration in the outcome widget. The application prompts for a DNC Start Time and a DNC End Time.
agent.TimeZone.Content: A campaign-specific flag to tell the API consumer on which time zone to be used to calculate DNC duration. If it is switched ON, the agent desktop should arrive the End date/time based on customer time then it should convert this timestamp into server time zone and pass it to setCallResults API. If this option is switched off, then the end should be arrived based on server time zone and pass it to setCallResults API.
agent.DNCType.label: DNC Type:
agent.DNCTypeinfo.content: A campaign-specific flag available to API consumer – the DNC type preferred for this campaign. Pass the appropriate parameter for the SetCallResults API. See below:
agent.CampaignSpecific.content: 1) Campaign Specific - If the flag is “CampaignSpecific”, pass CampaignSpecificDNC as “C” and DNCCampaignCategoryID as the phone number is marked for DNC only for the current campaign
agent.CampaignCategory.content: 2) Campaign Category - If the flag is “CampaignCategory”, pass CampaignSpecificDNC as “G” and the DNCCampaignCategoryID as current campaign category ID; the phone number as DNC for the specific campaign category.
agent.MultipleCategory.content: 3) Multiple Category - If the flag is “MultipleCategory”, pass CampaignSpecificDNC as “G” and the DNCCampaignCategoryID as selected campaign category IDs separated  by commas as the API parameter; the contact is marked as DNC only for the categories that are selected by the agent.
agent.Global.content: 4) Global - If the flag is “Global”, the API leaves the above parameters blank, so that the contact is marked as DNC across the system (both campaigns and categories).
